{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:galatians.5",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 5 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:1",
      "text": "Stand firm therefore in the liberty by which Christ has made us free, and don’ t be entangled again with a yoke of bondage.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:2",
      "text": "Behold, I, Paul, tell you that if you receive circumcision, Christ will profit you nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:3",
      "text": "Yes, I testify again to every man who receives circumcision that he is a debtor to do the whole law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:4",
      "text": "You are alienated from Christ, you who desire to be justified by the law. You have fallen away from grace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:5",
      "text": "For we through the Spirit, by faith wait for the hope of righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:6",
      "text": "For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision nor uncircumcision amounts to anything, but faith working through love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:7",
      "text": "You were running well! Who interfered with you that you should not obey the truth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:8",
      "text": "This persuasion is not from him who calls you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:9",
      "text": "A little yeast grows through the whole lump.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:10",
      "text": "I have confidence toward you in the Lord that you will think no other way. But he who troubles you will bear his judgment, whoever he is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:11",
      "text": "But I, brothers, if I still preach circumcision, why am I still persecuted? Then the stumbling block of the cross has been removed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:12",
      "text": "I wish that those who disturb you would cut themselves off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:13",
      "text": "For you, brothers, were called for freedom. Only don’ t use your freedom as an opportunity for the flesh, but through love be servants to one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:14",
      "text": "For the whole law is fulfilled in one word, in this: “ You shall love your neighbor as yourself.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:15",
      "text": "But if you bite and devour one another, be careful that you don’t consume one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:16",
      "text": "But I say, walk by the Spirit, and you won’t fulfill the lust of the flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:17",
      "text": "For the flesh lusts against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh; and these are contrary to one another, that you may not do the things that you desire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:18",
      "text": "But if you are led by the Spirit, you are not under the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:19",
      "text": "Now the deeds of the flesh are obvious, which are: adultery, sexual immorality, uncleanness, lustfulness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:20",
      "text": "idolatry, sorcery, hatred, strife, jealousies, outbursts of anger, rivalries, divisions, heresies,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:21",
      "text": "envy, murders, drunkenness, orgies, and things like these; of which I forewarn you, even as I also forewarned you, that those who practice such things will not inherit God ’s Kingdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:22",
      "text": "But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faith,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:23",
      "text": "gentleness, and self-control. Against such things there is no law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:24",
      "text": "Those who belong to Christ have crucified the flesh with its passions and lusts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:25",
      "text": "If we live by the Spirit, let ’s also walk by the Spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:galatians.5.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:26",
      "text": "Let ’s not become conceited, provoking one another, and envying one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
